Ang Lee
2013-02-24 15:59:03 GMT
Ang Lee is a Taiwanese-born American film director, screenwriter and producer.Lee has directed a diverse set of films such as Sense and Sensibility (1995), Crouching Tiger, Hidden Dragon (2000), which won the Academy Award for Best Foreign Language Film, Hulk (2003), Brokeback Mountain (2005), for which he won an Academy Award for Best Director and most recently Life of Pi (2012). He is the first person of Asian descent to win the Best Director Oscar.
